# Package Simplicity - Keep It Minimal

Agent Court follows **radical simplification** principles. Avoid creating unnecessary packages or complexity.

## Current Structure (Keep This Way)

```
packages/
└── sdk-js/             # Only external package needed
```

## What We Removed (Don't Recreate)

- ❌ **sdk-py** (No Python)
- ❌ **constitution** package (Hardcoded in [constitution.ts](mdc:apps/convex/constitution.ts))
- ❌ **mcp-server** package (Built into [http.ts](mdc:apps/convex/http.ts))
- ❌ **evidence** package (Logic in [sdk-js](mdc:packages/sdk-js/))
- ❌ **transparency** package (Functions in [transparency.ts](mdc:apps/convex/transparency.ts))

## When to Create New Packages

Only create new packages for:
- ✅ **External developer SDKs** (like sdk-js)
- ✅ **Reusable utilities** needed by multiple external projects
- ✅ **Language-specific integrations** (if absolutely necessary)

## What to Build Into Core Instead

Always build into [apps/convex/](mdc:apps/convex/) instead of separate packages:
- Court logic and rules
- Database schemas and types
- HTTP API endpoints
- Administrative functions
- Internal utilities

## Default Answer

When considering "Should this be a package?", the answer is usually **NO** - build it into the core Convex deployment instead.